race.comment: SOUTHERN CRESCENT (6) turned the most recent form around narrowly beaten here first-up. Looks to be back on track and will be fitter. Maps for a soft run and Hill sticks and will give her every chance. RUBIQUITY (2) resumed at Donald well supported but settled too far back in a strong form race. Has been kept on the fresh side and Coffey stays aboard. Has a low gate and a much better effort is on the cards. FUGACITY (4) has been plainer since the narrow defeat at Donald three back. Raced favourite last time and Rawiller rides on the quick backup. In the mix. SWEET CHEVAL (7) will skip over and ride the speed. Missed a lip from the front at Colac last time and will give a big sight. IRISH BLISS (1) resumes and has switched from a NSW yard. Will race over further but has some talent and is worth a betting watch.
